URL:-https://www.ndtv.com/business/foreign-exchange-reserves-at-new-life-time-high-of-437-83-billion-2115436



TITLE:
Foreign Exchange Reserves At New Life-Time High Of $437.83 Billion


Content:
FCA increased by $3.99 billion to $405.61 billion in the week ended October 4, the RBI said.Content:
The country's foreign exchange reserves surged by $4.24 billion to touch a record high of $437.83 billion in the week to October 4, according to the latest data from the Reserve Bank of India.Content:
In the previous week, the reserves had surged by massive $5.02 billion to $433.59 billion. The increase in reserves in the reporting week was on account of rise in foreign currency assets (FCA), a major component of the overall reserves.Content:
FCA increased by $3.99 billion to $405.61 billion in the week ended October 4, the RBI said.Content:
Expressed in US dollar terms, the foreign currency assets include the effect of appreciation or depreciation of non-US units like the euro, pound and the yen held in the foreign exchange reserves.Content:
During the week, gold reserves increased $232 million to $27.17 billion. The special drawing rights with the International Monetary Fund were up by $1 million to $1.43 billion during the week.Content:
The country's reserve position with the IMF also increased by $9 million to $3.61 billion, the data showed.Content:
